29 May 2016 On Monday, 30 May at 09h00, The Financial Fiscal Commission (FFC) will brief the media on the annual submission for the division of revenue 2017/2018. The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town, with a link up to GCIS, Tshedimosetso House, Pretoria.On Wednesday, 01 June at 11h00, The Auditor-General of South Africa, Kimi Makwetu will brief the media on the release of the audit results of the country s municipalities for the financial year 2014-15. The briefing will be held at GCIS, Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria with a link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town.On Thursday, 02 June at 11h00, The Statistician-General, Dr Pali Lehohla will brief the media on the release of the findings of the General Household Survey 2015. The survey provides the latest statistics on education, health, the labour market, dwellings, access to services and facilities, transport, and the quality of life in South Africa. The briefing will be held at GCIS, Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria with a link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town.In addition to these media briefings, Ministers participate in various public events and for a comprehensive list of national and provincial government activities kindly visit www.gov.za. Should there be changes in the information above, members of the media will be notified accordingly.Enquiries: Mzobanzi Jikazana Cell: 083 641 2355Issued by Government Communication and Information System